shared_text:
Godwin Heights Public Schools
July 15 at 12:58 PM ·

Online Enrollment Now Open - Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, Godwin Heights Public Schools will not have an Enrollment Extravaganza in August. Instead, the district has moved to Online Registration for the 2020-21 school year. Please log into your family’s ParentVue account, click on Online Registration (top right corner) to complete the registration process for the 2020-21 school year. You will have to do this from a computer or Chromebook. All families must verify and make any changes needed to their student's personal information no later than August 1st. If you need technical assistance navigating through the online process or still have additional questions, please email online@godwinschools.org to receive help enrolling your student. Thank you for choosing Godwin Heights Public Schools! http://edl.io/n1256462
text:
Godwin Heights Public Schools
July 15 at 12:58 PM ·

Online Enrollment Now Open - Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, Godwin Heights Public Schools will not have an Enrollment Extravaganza in August. Instead, the district has moved to Online Registration for the 2020-21 school year. Please log into your family’s ParentVue account, click on Online Registration (top right corner) to complete the registration process for the 2020-21 school year. You will have to do this from a computer or Chromebook. All families must verify and make any changes needed to their student's personal information no later than August 1st. If you need technical assistance navigating through the online process or still have additional questions, please email online@godwinschools.org to receive help enrolling your student. Thank you for choosing Godwin Heights Public Schools! http://edl.io/n1256462

post_text:
Tomorrow, Wednesday, June 24 is the day for free food! Come to North Godwin Elementary between 10:30 and 12:30 and we will give you 14 meals (7 breakfast and 7 lunch) for each child in your family under the age of 18! We packed thousands of bags today so we’re ready for you! You will enter the parking lot on the north end and drive through to get your food. Can’t wait to see you all! Spread the word!

¡Mañana miércoles 24 de junio es el día de la comida gratis! ¡Venga a North Godwin Elementary entre las 10:30 y las 12:30 y le daremos 14 comidas (7 desayunos y 7 almuerzos) por cada niño de su familia menor de 18 años! ¡Empacamos miles de bolsas hoy, así que estamos listos para ti! Entrará al estacionamiento en el extremo norte y conducirá para obtener su comida. ¡No puedo esperar para verlos a todos! ¡Difundir la palabra!

NAACP Grand Rapids
May 6 at 10:02 PM ·

This coming Saturday May 9 , from 1pm-3pm NAACPR will be providing 200+ local families with FREE food and cleaning supply care packages. If you or someone you know are in need and interested in receiving a care package please confirm by texting the keyword "Relief" to the number 8338273478. Once you confirm instructions and directions will be provided to you. Please be prepared to accommodate for 50 pounds of food.

El Greater Grand Rapids NAACP ofrecerá paquetes de asistencia a más de 200 familias e individuos locales que necesiten comida, máscaras y artículos de limpieza. Las mercancías se distribuirán en un estilo de servicio al carro. Prepárese para tener espacio para acomodar 50 libras de comestibles.

post_text: Thank You! - Thanks to your yes votes, students will have access to technology, transportation, and facilities that will support high-quality teaching and learning! We are grateful to our community for finding a way to vote even under such difficult circumstances. Thank you for demonstrating your commitment to education and our collective future. Today, Wednesday, April 29 is the day for free food! Come to North Godwin Elementary between 10:30 and 12:30 and we will give you 14 meals (7 breakfast and 7 lunch) for each child in your family under the age of 18! We packed thousands of bags today so we’re ready for you! You will enter the parking lot on the north end and drive through to get your food. Can’t wait to see you all! Spread the word!

¡Miércoles 29 de abril es el día de la comida gratis! ¡Venga a North Godwin Elementary entre las 10:30 y las 12:30 y le daremos 14 comidas (7 desayunos y 7 almuerzos) por cada niño de su familia menor de 18 años! ¡Empacamos miles de bolsas hoy, así que estamos listos para ti! Entrará al estacionamiento en el extremo norte y conducirá para obtener su comida. ¡No puedo esperar para verlos a todos! ¡Difundir la palabra!

shared_text:
Michigan Department of Health and Human Services
March 28 at 9:42 AM ·

In response to the COVID-19 outbreak, households eligible for food assistance will receive additional benefits in March and April to bring all current SNAP cases to the maximum monthly allowance for that group size.

This change only applies to customers not currently receiving the maximum benefit amount.

350,000 eligible families will see additional food assistance benefits on their Bridge Card by Monday, March 30. Eligible families do not need to re-apply to receive additional benefits. Learn more at https://bit.ly/2UJsnop.

FREE Internet for 2 months - new, qualifying Comcast customers - Qualifying new customers in a Comcast service area will receive 60 days of complimentary Internet Essentials service. You may qualify if you are eligible for public assistance programs such as the National School Lunch Program, Housing Assistance, Medicaid, SNAP, SSI, and others.
Once you are an Internet Essentials customer, you have the option to purchase a laptop or desktop computer at a discounted price of $149.99+ Tax.
Read the full story for a link to more information. http://edl.io/n1185289
